            <h2>MANAGEMENT Bio's</h2>
            <h3>

<a href="mailto:mberneis@syncit.com">

<b>

Michael Berneis</b></a>, President and Founder&nbsp;
</h3>
            <p>
Michael Berneis formerly managed intranet technology design for the New York Stock Exchange
(<a href="http://www.nyse.com/" target="_blank">NYSE</a>), where he produced a remote detection system which tracks insider-trading activity on the Internet, a secure Internet data-entry system for member firms of the NYSE, and a natural language query-based system to manage internal trading rules and arbitrate legal disputes from the trading floor. Prior to NYSE, Berneis designed real-time streaming video solutions for advertising agency Intranet products and built an Intranet system for high volume delivery of advertising video and image data. Earlier in his career, Berneis worked at
<a href="http://www.reuters.com" target="_blank">Reuters</a>, building Intranet applications for real-time trading data displays and a prototype of a futuristic trading station. Prior to Reuters, Berneis headed up research &amp; development for
<a href="http://fast-multimedia.com" target="_blank"> Fast Multimedia AG in
Munich</a>, a producer of digital video editing systems.
</p>
            <h3><a href="mailto:tway@syncit.com"><b>Terence Way</b></a>, Chief Technology Officer and Co-Founder&nbsp;
</h3>
            <p>
Terry has 14 years experience in the software development industry.  Prior to SyncIT, Terry was a senior software architect at
            <a href="http://www.reuters.com" target="_blank"> Reuters</a> for seven years, with primary responsibility for identifying Internet opportunities.  One example of this is the development of a real-time world map showing the traffic on the Reuters Dealing foreign exchange system - details of which can be found in the book Java for Business by Thomas Anderson.  He also worked on the initial release of the
            <a href="http://www.alertnet.org" target="_blank"> AlertNet web site</a>. Prior to Reuters, Terry developed high volume financial software systems, including TMX, transactional message and database system, responsible for 800 billion USD a day in funds transfer; The Supervisor Series - utility software that monitors and records user terminals on VAX/VMS machines; and MoneyMatch, a currency-trading platform, which was sold to Reuters.&nbsp;
</p>
